[ProMED maps of Australia https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8706948,186 and Singapore https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8706948,150]

[Low vaccination rates in a world reopening from COVID-19 combined with increasing international travel continue to help measles not only spread locally but move to locations with pockets of unvaccinated children susceptible to the highly infectious measles virus. We can only hope vaccination rates quickly rebound globally, but with public health resources (and especially funding) continuing to be stretched by COVID-19, monkeypox, and Sudan Ebolavirus surveillance and response activities, it is unclear how long it may take to return to "normal" on the measles-prevention front. - Mod.JH]
